        "created_at": "2020-08-11T10:34:12.000Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group quote-modified\" data-post=\"3\" data-topic=\"163202\">\n<blockquote>\n<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-post=\"2\" data-topic=\"163202\">\n<blockquote>\n<p>have you listened to podcasts with Morgan from Bedrock?  Bedrock has some podcasts where he goes through some vineyard history and his podcast with Levi on I\u2019ll drink to that is loaded with info.</p>\n<p>I know its not reading, but I learned a lot from them.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>I\u2019ve listened to both! But great idea.  There are definitely some other instructive IDTT episodes that cover Sonoma, all of which I\u2019ve listened to.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>agreed.</p>\n<p>if you want some SERIOUS history, have you checked out the Roadside Terroir podcast as well?  It\u2019s Brenna Quigley\u2019s podcast, a geologist who specializes in wine terroir.</p>",
