      {
        "id": 2955092,
        "name": "Benjamin Hand",
        "username": "Benjamin_Hand",
        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/b/ecccb3/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2020-08-12T00:04:44.000Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-post=\"5\" data-topic=\"163202\">\n<blockquote>\n<p>agreed.</p>\n<p>if you want some SERIOUS history, have you checked out the Roadside Terroir podcast as well?  It\u2019s Brenna Quigley\u2019s podcast, a geologist who specializes in wine terroir.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>That\u2019s a great tip.  I loved the episode that Levi did with her on IDTT.  It combined my love of John McPhee\u2019s writings on geology with my interest in wine.</p>",
