      {
        "id": 2955095,
        "name": null,
        "username": "Mattstolz",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/mattstolz/{size}/2820_2.png",
        "created_at": "2020-08-12T00:07:48.000Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group quote-modified\" data-post=\"7\" data-topic=\"163202\">\n<blockquote>\n<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-post=\"5\" data-topic=\"163202\">\n<blockquote>\n<p>agreed.</p>\n<p>if you want some SERIOUS history, have you checked out the Roadside Terroir podcast as well?  It\u2019s Brenna Quigley\u2019s podcast, a geologist who specializes in wine terroir.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>That\u2019s a great tip.  I loved the episode that Levi did with her on IDTT.  It combined my love of John McPhee\u2019s writings on geology with my interest in wine.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>the first episode is definitely more setting the stage as a broad Sonoma geology overview but the second one starts to talk a little more about individual vineyards and start to bring some winemakers into the discussion. both are interesting.</p>",
